        <div n="397-ROGP" type="poem"><head type="note" n="1" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-headnote-1"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-headnote-1-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="2" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-headnote-2"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-headnote-2-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head><head type="note" n="3" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-headnote-3"><lg n="1" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1" type="headnote"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-headnote-3-line-group-1-line-1"/></lg></head>
      <lg n="1" type="stanza"><l n="1" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-1">Mordanto fills the trump of fame,&#13;</l><l n="2" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-2"> The Christian world his deeds proclaim,</l><l n="3" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-3"> And prints are crowded with his name.</l></lg><lg n="2" type="stanza"><l n="4" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-4">In journeys he outrides the post,&#13;</l><l n="5" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-5"> Sits up till midnight with his host,</l><l n="6" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-6"> Talks politics, and gives the toast.</l></lg><lg n="3" type="stanza"><l n="7" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-7">Knows every prince in Europe's face,&#13;</l><l n="8" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-8"> Flies like a squib from place to place,</l><l n="9" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-9"> And travels not, but runs a race.</l></lg><lg n="4" type="stanza"><l n="10" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-10">From Paris Gazette <hi rend="underline">Ã  la main</hi>,</l><l n="11" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-11"> This day arrived without his train,</l><l n="12" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-12"> Mordanto in a week from Spain.</l></lg><lg n="5" type="stanza"><l n="13" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-13">A messenger comes all a-reek,&#13;</l><l n="14" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-14"> Mordanto at Madrid to seek:</l><l n="15" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-15"> He left the town above a week.Next day the post-boy winds his horn,</l><l n="16" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-16"> And rides through Dover in the morn:</l><l n="17" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-17"> Mordanto's landed from Leghorn.</l></lg><lg n="6" type="stanza"><l n="18" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-18">Mordanto gallops on alone,&#13;</l><l n="19" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-19"> The roads are with his followers strewn,</l><l n="20" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-20"> This breaks a girth, and that a bone.</l></lg><lg n="7" type="stanza"><l n="21" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-21">His body active as his mind,&#13;</l><l n="22" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-22"> Returning sound in limb and wind,</l><l n="23" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-23"> Except some leather lost behind.</l></lg><lg n="8" type="stanza"><l n="24" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-24">A skeleton in outward figure,&#13;</l><l n="25" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-25"> His meagre corpse, though full of vigour,</l><l n="26" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-26"> Would halt behind him, were it bigger.</l></lg><lg n="9" type="stanza"><l n="27" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-27">So wonderful his expedition,&#13;</l><l n="28" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-28"> When you have not the least suspicion,</l><l n="29" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-29"> He's with you like an apparition.</l></lg><lg n="10" type="stanza"><l n="30" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-30">Shines in all climates like a star;&#13;</l><l n="31" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-31"> In senates bold, and fierce in war,</l><l n="32" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-32"> A land commander, and a tar.</l></lg><lg n="11" type="stanza"><l n="33" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-33">Heroic actions early bred in,&#13;</l><l n="34" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-34"> Ne'er to be matched in modern reading,</l><l n="35" xml:id="spp-397-ROGP-line-35"> But by his namesake Charles of Sweden.397-ROGP   </l></lg></div>
